# Keep comments

`djot.js` has a djot renderer already,
you can use it to format a djot file like this:

``` bash
djot -f djot -t djot
```

It will remove all comments in the output file,
as comments are not emitted as an event at all.

But djotfmt will keep comments in the output file.

